     4	
     5	- Role drift risk: the academic UI computes `allowedRoles` from proof-scoped bootstrap data while the session keeps its own active grants. A role can disappear from the UI without disappearing from the session.
     6	- Role drift risk: `canAccessPage()` and the route sync logic can briefly accept a deep link and then snap it back to the role home page, which can mask route-level exposure in manual testing.
     7	- Authorization blind spot: `Faculty Profile`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are easy to reach indirectly, but each has a backend scope gate that is narrower than the visible UI label suggests.

