@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@
+# Role Surface Pass
+
+Date: 2026-04-15
+
+## Result
+
+Mapped the scoped role surface across the academic portal and sysadmin portal, with UI visibility separated from backend authorization.
+
+## Key Findings
+
+- `Course Leader`, `Mentor`, `HoD`, and `SYSTEM_ADMIN` have distinct visible UI surfaces, but the backend gates are narrower and role-specific.
+- `faculty-profile`, `student-shell`, `risk-explorer`, and `unlock-review` are the main indirect access paths that matter for drift review.
+- Academic role switching is session-backed, but the teaching UI trims the visible role set from proof-scoped bootstrap data.
+- `SYSTEM_ADMIN` remains the only role that can use the full admin control plane and proof sandbox routes.
+
+## Files Updated
+
+- `audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md`
+- `audit-map/24-agent-memory/known-facts.md`
+- `audit-map/24-agent-memory/known-ambiguities.md`
+- `audit-map/15-final-maps/critical-risks.md`
+- `audit-map/23-coverage/coverage-ledger.md`

diff --git a/audit-map/15-final-maps/critical-risks.md b/audit-map/15-final-maps/critical-risks.md
index 3f8f4e7a6f66c63cae0dd546f1e5d98dc5befee6..4504616b9a62c58269bc34fb9db920ee891ebbe8
--- a/audit-map/15-final-maps/critical-risks.md
+++ b/audit-map/15-final-maps/critical-risks.md
@@ -1,3 +1,7 @@
 # Critical Risks
 
 Aggregate the highest-risk contradictions, stale assumptions, and blind spots here.
+
+- Role drift risk: the academic UI computes `allowedRoles` from proof-scoped bootstrap data while the session keeps its own active grants. A role can disappear from the UI without disappearing from the session.
+- Role drift risk: `canAccessPage()` and the route sync logic can briefly accept a deep link and then snap it back to the role home page, which can mask route-level exposure in manual testing.
+- Authorization blind spot: `Faculty Profile`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are easy to reach indirectly, but each has a backend scope gate that is narrower than the visible UI label suggests.
diff --git a/audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md b/audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md
index 60e805d5caff492f1a60711cc625a6c9a7dcff44..bb7a18659961549baa58f54be4ede464db36af9a
--- a/audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md
+++ b/audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md
@@ -1,3 +1,49 @@
 # Role Feature Matrix
 
-Map each role to each verified feature and note local/live/test status.
+Pass: `role-surface-pass`
+Date: 2026-04-15
+
+Map each role to the visible UI it can reach, the backend authorization that actually applies, and the hidden or indirect paths that can still expose the same surface.
+
+## Role Matrix
+
+| Role | Visible UI | Backend authorization | Hidden or indirect paths | Notes |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Public / unauthenticated | Portal chooser, academic login screen, sysadmin login screen, public faculty list | Only the public faculty list is open (`GET /api/academic/public/faculty`); session, bootstrap, and admin APIs require auth | `#/app` and `#/admin` still render portal shells, but the workspaces immediately block on session state | No protected workspace state is available without a session. |
+| Course Leader | `Dashboard`, `Queue History`, `Calendar / Timetable`, `Data Entry Hub`, course pages, student pages, faculty profile button | Session login and `POST /api/session/role-context`; `GET /api/academic/bootstrap`; course-leader-owned offering reads/writes; `tasks`, `task-placements`, `calendar-audit`, `meetings`, and offering config routes are scope-gated; `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` require active-run + student scope | `scheme-setup` and `entry-workspace` are launched from course/upload actions; `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are launched from student cards and proof controls | Visible UI is broader than backend write scope. The page helper can show a route, but the server still checks offering ownership and student enrollment. |
+| Mentor | `My Mentees`, `Queue History`, `Calendar / Timetable`, faculty profile button | Session login and `role-context`; `GET /api/academic/bootstrap`; mentor-scoped task and meeting creation; `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` require active-run + student scope | `mentee-detail`, `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are reached from mentee cards and history links, not from top-level nav | Mentor UI is narrow, but indirect student drilldowns remain first-class routes. |
+| HoD | `Department`, `Queue History`, `Calendar / Timetable`, unlock-review actions in the queue, faculty profile button | Session login and `role-context`; `GET /api/academic/bootstrap`; HoD proof bundle endpoints; governed request list/create; faculty profile reads with department/branch overlap checks; HOD-scoped offering and student access checks; `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` require active-run + student scope | `unlock-review` is not a top-level nav item but is opened from queue actions or direct hashes; `faculty-profile` can target any faculty only when the overlap check passes | HoD is the only academic role with dedicated proof-summary/bundle/courses/faculty/students/reassessments reads. |
+| SYSTEM_ADMIN | `#/admin` overview, proof dashboard, faculties, students, faculty members, requests, history, and canonical proof hierarchy drilldowns | All `/api/admin/*` families, proof sandbox routes, session restore/logout/role-context, academic bootstrap, `faculty-profile` self/admin/HOD read path, `student-shell`, `risk-explorer`, and preferences | `#/admin/faculties/:.../batches/:...` is the canonical proof route; `#/admin/history` is the hidden-records surface; search can route into students, faculty, and requests without using the visible tabs | `SystemAdminSessionBoundary` blocks the workspace unless the active session role is `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, even if the user is logged in under another grant. |
+
+## Permission Gates
+
+- `canAccessPage()` is a client-side gate only. It keeps the academic router from staying on a disallowed page, but it does not replace backend auth.
+- `resolveRoleSyncState()` snaps disallowed role/page combinations back to the role home page.
+- `/api/session/role-context` only switches among the session's `availableRoleGrants`; it does not mint a new grant.
+- `requireRole()` is the first backend gate on the protected routes. It checks the active grant only.
+- `assertViewerCanReadOffering()`, `assertViewerCanSuperviseStudent()`, `assertCourseLeaderCanManageOffering()`, `resolveProofReassessmentAccess()`, and `evaluateStudentShellSessionMessageAccess()` add the role/scope-specific checks.
+- `GET /api/academic/faculty-profile/:facultyId` is self-access for the same faculty, or HoD/admin access with a department/branch overlap check.
+- `GET /api/academic/hod/proof-*` endpoints require `HOD` plus faculty context.
+- `GET /api/academic/student-shell/*` and `GET /api/academic/students/:studentId/risk-explorer` accept academic roles and `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, but still enforce proof-run and student-scope checks.
+
+## Hidden Or Indirect Access Paths
+
+- The academic sidebar always exposes a `Faculty Profile` button, but backend access is still self/HOD/admin scoped.
+- `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are cross-cutting routes reached from student cards, mentee cards, queue rows, and proof controls.
+- `unlock-review` is reachable from queue actions and direct hashes, even though it is not a top-level sidebar item.
+- `#/admin/proof-dashboard` and the canonical proof hierarchy route are route-level entry points, not visible top tabs.
+- `#/admin/history` is a hidden-records workspace, but admin search can still surface requests from that section.
+- Academic role options in the teaching portal are derived from the current bootstrap snapshot, so proof scope can hide roles that still exist in the underlying session.
+
+## Role Drift Likely
+
+- The academic UI derives `allowedRoles` from the proof-scoped bootstrap, while `/api/session/role-context` uses the underlying session grants. That can make a role appear unavailable in the UI even when it is still switchable.
+- The app auto-corrects illegal pages back to the role home page, so a deep link can briefly exist in history without being durable.
+- `Faculty Profile` is visibly available to every academic role, but the backend rejects out-of-scope HoD reads, so the UI affordance is broader than the authorization surface.
+- `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` are easy to reach indirectly, but their server-side scope checks are stricter than the route names imply.
+
+## Role-Specific Unknowns
+
+- The exact narrowing behavior of `resolveStudentShellRun()` and `assertStudentShellScope()` still needs live confirmation.
+- The live proof-scoped bootstrap may hide some active session grants in the UI, but the session still retains them; the full impact on role switching is only partially verified.
+- The HoD faculty-profile overlap check is confirmed by test coverage, but the live deployment path still needs an authenticated end-to-end check.
