+# Role Surface Pass
+
+Date: 2026-04-15
+
+## Result
+
+Mapped the scoped role surface across the academic portal and sysadmin portal, with UI visibility separated from backend authorization.
+
+## Key Findings
+
+- `Course Leader`, `Mentor`, `HoD`, and `SYSTEM_ADMIN` have distinct visible UI surfaces, but the backend gates are narrower and role-specific.
+- `faculty-profile`, `student-shell`, `risk-explorer`, and `unlock-review` are the main indirect access paths that matter for drift review.
+- Academic role switching is session-backed, but the teaching UI trims the visible role set from proof-scoped bootstrap data.
+- `SYSTEM_ADMIN` remains the only role that can use the full admin control plane and proof sandbox routes.
+
+## Files Updated
+
+- `audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md`
+- `audit-map/24-agent-memory/known-facts.md`
